Program: The History Hour
Title: Iceland jails its bankers
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3cswqmv
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 19 Feb 2019
Why Iceland jailed 40 bankers after the 2008 financial crisis, how the Maastricht Treaty gave birth to the EU, plus America's first female airline pilots, Cameroon's historic referendum and homeless, drunk and yet a genius in the USSR. (Photo: Protesters on the streets of Reykjavik demand answers from the government and the banks about the country's financial crisis, Nov. 2008. (Halldor Kolbeins/AFP/Getty Images) Show less